{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"eclectic-spotted-barb","description":"# Concurrent review-plan silently drops the plan-review attestation: enrich_drain._prune_queue_events uses an unlocked whole-index git commit that races locked store writes\n\n## Summary\n\nUnder `[agents]`, every `review-plan` finish triggers the opportunistic enrichment drain, whose\n`rebar.llm.enrich_drain._prune_queue_events` (`src/rebar/llm/enrich_drain.py:191-207`) stages and\ncommits with a **raw, unlocked, whole-index** `git rm` + `git commit` — taking neither the unified\nstore write lock nor a commit pathspec. Running in the detached drain child concurrently with a\nreview's locked `stage_and_commit` writes, it drops the concurrent writer's event, so a PASS\nreview leaves NO persisted attestation (and no observability sidecar).\n\nThis is the un-hardened twin of bug `malevolent-emigratory-umbrette`, whose fix routed the two\nsibling prunes (`plan_review/sidecar.py:94`, `overlap/digest_sidecar.py:141`) through the locked,\npathspec-scoped `event_append.delete_events`; the enrich-queue prune was missed.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. Concurrently run `rebar review-plan` on several DIFFERENT tickets (separate processes), with the\n   `[agents]` extra + a real key (so the enrichment drain is live).\n2. Some PASS reviews return `sidecar_emitted=False` and `verify-signature` → \"unsigned — ticket has\n   no signature\", despite a PASS verdict. Serial runs persist fine.\n\nConfirmed by an isolated-store experiment (remote OFF, so branch-divergence is excluded): 6 locked\n`append_event` writers vs 4 processes calling the real `_prune_queue_events` produced 33/360 writes\nraising `git commit failed while holding lock` (\"nothing to commit\" — the writer's staged blob was\nswept into the prune's whole-index commit — and \"cannot lock ref 'HEAD': is at X but expected Y\"),\nwith all 33 blobs left IN HEAD but UNLINKED from the worktree (sweep-and-strand); worktree-listing\nreaders then report them absent.\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n\n- **Expected:** a concurrent write is serialized by the single store write lock (invariant I5); a\n  committed event is durable and visible to readers. \"A push failure never fails the write — the\n  commit stays local\" (CLAUDE.md). A PASS review persists a claimable attestation.\n- **Actual:** the unlocked prune committer sweeps/orphans a concurrent locked write; the review's\n  own commit fails (swallowed by `sidecar.emit` → `sidecar_emitted=False` and by\n  `attest.sign_plan_review` → unsigned), and the swept blob is unlinked from the worktree.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`_prune_queue_events` performs a store write OUTSIDE the unified write lock with a whole-index\ncommit, contrary to `event_append.delete_events`'s contract (`event_append.py:302-307`) and the I5\nsingle-lock invariant (`_store/lock.py:1-24`).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `src/rebar/llm/enrich_drain.py:_prune_queue_events` no longer runs a raw unlocked `git rm` /\n  whole-index `git commit`; it routes through the locked, pathspec-scoped\n  `event_append.delete_events` (mirroring `plan_review/sidecar.py:prune`).\n  - Proving: `rg -n 'subprocess.run.*git' src/rebar/llm/enrich_drain.py` shows no raw `git commit`\n    in `_prune_queue_events`; `rg -n 'delete_events' src/rebar/llm/enrich_drain.py` present.\n- [ ] A regression test reproduces the race (RED before the fix) and passes after: concurrent\n  locked writes + the drain-queue prune leave zero dropped/stranded events.\n  - Proving: the new test in `tests/` fails on `origin/main` and passes with the fix; `make test` green.\n- [ ] A sibling sweep confirms no other unlocked `git commit` store-write remains outside the\n  locked path.\n  - Proving: `rg -n \"git.*commit\" src/rebar --glob '*.py'` reviewed; any raw store-commit routes\n    through the locked path or is justified.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass (CI's Verified gate green on the change).","id":"3435-c833-4a43-42ae","parent_id":"","priority":1,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"Concurrent review-plan silently drops the plan-review attestation: enrich_drain._prune_queue_events uses an unlocked whole-index git commit that races locked store writes"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784239407145811001,"uuid":"0568fea4-1db0-4f2b-b4b2-99d8b02ff974"}